<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/LeachingOperation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "MWEI BREF : Extraction of soluble components from raw materials by the action of a percolating liquid (e.g. water). For example, gold can be extracted by heap \nleaching of a porous ore, or pulverised extractive waste from mineral  processing. Other methods are tank leaching of ore, concentrates or extractive waste from mineral processing and in-situ leaching. Leaching may also be an unwanted process leading to polluted drainage (see \"leachate\"). Bio-leaching is a particular form of leaching involving living organisms"@en .
