# http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MillingOperation
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MillingOperation> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MillingOperation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MineralProcessingOperation> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MillingOperation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "MWEI BREF : Operation during which ore is treated for the recovery and/or concentration of valuable minerals prior to shipment to a smelter or refinery. Milling\nprocesses include crushing, grinding, screening, concentration and dewatering. At a coal mine, the mill is referred to as a wash plant, tipple or cleaner"@en .
# 
# http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Mine
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Mine> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Mine> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "MWEI BREF : Area under the control of an operator where mining occurs (see \"mining\"), \nincluding common related infrastructure and waste management activities."@en .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Mine> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "INSPIRE: An excavation carried out for the extraction of mineral deposits." .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Mine> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Subclass of INSPIRE Mine Feature" .
# 
# http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Mineral
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Mineral> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Mineral> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "METSO Handbook : Mineral is a natural inorganic substance precisely defined \naccording to its physical and chemical characteristics"@en .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Mineral> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "In the future, create a relation between mineral and metal to represent the chemical processes to do to extract the metal from the mineral.\n\nThis define on the basis of partner information.\nOn the current information which we received \"4 main questions we try to answer (which each require different methods):\" first 2 questions" .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Mineral> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Subclass of Commodity Measure\nIf cutOffGrade and Grade is unrelated to quality we have to put new properties related to quality" .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Mineral> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> "INSPIRE: Mineral is defined as any naturally occurring inorganic element or compound having a periodically repeating arrangement of atoms and a characteristic chemical composition or range of compositions, resulting in distinctive physical properties" .
# 
# http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MineralMeasurement
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MineralMeasurement> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MineralMeasurement> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Measurement> .
# 
# http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MineralProcessingOperation
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MineralProcessingOperation> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MineralProcessingOperation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Operation> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MineralProcessingOperation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "MWEI BREF : Mineral processing (also \nbeneficiation or \nbenefication, ore \ndressing, mineral \ndressing, milling) \nProcesses to produce marketable mineral products (e.g. concentrates) from \nmineral resources. This is usually carried out on the mine or quarry site, the \nplant being referred to as the mineral processing plant (mill or concentrator). \nThe essential purpose is to reduce the bulk of the ore, which must be \ntransported to and processed by subsequent processes (e.g. smelting), by \nusing methods to separate the valuable (desired) mineral(s) from the gangue. \nThe marketable product of this is called concentrate, the remaining material is \ncalled extractive waste from mineral processing (e.g. tailings).\nMineral processing includes various procedures that rely on the mineral's \nphysical characteristics (i.e. particle size, density, magnetic properties, colour) \nor physico-chemical properties (surface tension, hydrophobicity, wettability)."@en .
# 
# http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MineralogicalAnalysis
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MineralogicalAnalysis> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
# 
# http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MineralogicalAnalysisOperation
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MineralogicalAnalysisOperation> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MineralogicalAnalysisOperation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/LaboratoryAnalysisOperation> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MineralogicalAnalysisOperation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Determines the types and relative amounts of minerals within a material, providing insights into its composition, properties, and formation conditions" .
# 
# http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MineralogicalCharacteristics
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MineralogicalCharacteristics> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MineralogicalCharacteristics> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/core:Characteristics> .
# 
# http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MiningLCA
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MiningLCA> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MiningLCA> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/LCA> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MiningLCA> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "LCA in mining is a systematic method for identifying, quantifying, and evaluating the environmental impacts associated with the entire life cycle of mining-related processes and products, from exploration and extraction to processing, transportation, use, and end-of-life management." .
# 
# http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MiningWaste
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MiningWaste> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MiningWaste> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "MWEI BREF : Waste resulting from the prospecting, extraction, treatment and storage of \nmineral resources and the working of quarries"@en .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MiningWaste> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Mining activity exploits a mineral deposit, obtaining a concentrate (mineral object of the activity) and waste." .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MiningWaste> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Subclass of Mining Waste from INSPIRE ontology\n\nNote: for URI consult to INSPIRE Team" .
# 
# http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MiningWasteFacility
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MiningWasteFacility> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MiningWasteFacility> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "MWEI BREF : Any area under the responsibility of an operator where extractive waste is \nhandled, treated, accumulated or deposited whether in a solid or liquid state or \nin solution or suspension. This includes, but is not limited to, Extractive \nWaste Facilities, excavation voids where extractive waste is placed back, and \nareas for temporary storage of extractive waste."@en .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MiningWasteFacility> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A mining waste facility is a designated site or structure used to store extractive waste (includes materials like waste rock and tailings from mining and mineral processing operations)." .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MiningWasteFacility> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Mining Waste Facilities (MWF): (SCIMIN-GA)\ndefined by JRC as any area designated for the accumulation or deposit of extractive waste, whether in solid or liquid state or in solution or suspension, derived from extracting & processing mineral resources. \nReference Grant Agreement (GA).\n\nMining Waste (INSPIRE Model)\nMining waste can be defined as a part of the materials that result from the exploration, mining and processing of substances governed by legislation on mines and quarries." .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MiningWasteFacility> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "sublcass of mining wasting  from INSPIRE\n\nNote: for URI, we need to consult INSPIRE team because current it is not mentioned in specification document and nor on website" .
# 
# http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MiningWasteMeasurement
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MiningWasteMeasurement> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MiningWasteMeasurement> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Measurement> .
