# 
# http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/ProcessingEquipment
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/ProcessingEquipment> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/ProcessingEquipment> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Equipment> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/ProcessingEquipment> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "What machinery/equipment is suitable to achieve desired particle size." .
# 
# http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/ProcessingPlant
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/ProcessingPlant> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/ProcessingPlant> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "MWEI BREF : Facility where mineral processing is carried out.\nMineral processing (also \nbeneficiation or \nbenefication, ore \ndressing, mineral \ndressing, milling) \nProcesses to produce marketable mineral products (e.g. concentrates) from \nmineral resources. This is usually carried out on the mine or quarry site, the \nplant being referred to as the mineral processing plant (mill or concentrator). \nThe essential purpose is to reduce the bulk of the ore, which must be \ntransported to and processed by subsequent processes (e.g. smelting), by \nusing methods to separate the valuable (desired) mineral(s) from the gangue. \nThe marketable product of this is called concentrate, the remaining material is \ncalled extractive waste from mineral processing (e.g. tailings).\nMineral processing includes various procedures that rely on the mineral's \nphysical characteristics (i.e. particle size, density, magnetic properties, colour) \nor physico-chemical properties (surface tension, hydrophobicity, wettability)."@en .
# 
# http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Protocol
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Protocol> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Protocol> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/ControlMeasure> .
# 
# http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/PyroProcessingOperation
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/PyroProcessingOperation> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/PyroProcessingOperation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MineralProcessingOperation> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/PyroProcessingOperation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "METSO Handbook : Pyro processing includes the technologies for upgrading of the mineral fractions by drying, calcining or sintering."@en .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/PyroProcessingOperation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "MWEI BREF : Incineration is a high-temperature combustion/oxidation process in which organic wastes are converted into gases and solid residue. Incineration \nobjectives usually include reducing toxicity and volume prior to disposal of \nsolid residues."@en .
